The article discusses the potential economic effects of the tax reforms proposed by President Trump's administration. The authors argue that reducing corporate tax rates and lowering individual tax rates would increase economic activity and generate federal tax revenue. They believe that these reforms would lead to increased investment, GDP growth, and higher household incomes. The authors also emphasize the importance of confirming a pro-growth objective for tax reform. Overall, they assert that the proposed tax reforms would enhance economic growth and reduce the static cost of lost federal tax revenue.